abstract: High school cross-country runners were starting their afternoon run on Monday when a pickup truck plowed into them, killing two students.
snippet: High school cross-country runners were starting their afternoon run on Monday when a pickup truck plowed into them, killing two students.
lead_paragraph: MOORE, Okla. — A day after losing his son in a car wreck, a grieving father drove his pickup truck onto a crowded sidewalk near a suburban high school outside of Oklahoma City, killing two teenagers and plunging the community into a wider circle of grief.

abstract: Joe Biden's third presidential bid enters a critical stretch after a disappointing finish in the Iowa caucuses sent the former vice president on to New Hampshire with a skittish donor base, low cash reserves and the looming threat of billionaire rival Michael Bloomberg and his unlimited personal wealth.
snippet: Joe Biden's third presidential bid enters a critical stretch after a disappointing finish in the Iowa caucuses sent the former vice president on to New Hampshire with a skittish donor base, low cash reserves and the looming threat of billionaire r...
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Joe Biden's third presidential bid enters a critical stretch after a disappointing finish in the Iowa caucuses sent the former vice president on to New Hampshire with a skittish donor base, low cash reserves and the looming threat of billionaire rival Michael Bloomberg and his unlimited personal wealth.
headline_main: Biden's Poor Showing in Iowa Shakes Establishment Support
headline_print_headline: Biden's Poor Showing in Iowa Shakes Establishment Support

abstract: In an era when few if any producers were women, she got access to the Kremlin, China and more.
snippet: In an era when few if any producers were women, she got access to the Kremlin, China and more.
lead_paragraph: Lucy Jarvis, a groundbreaking producer in television and theater who was especially known for gaining access to hard-to-crack locations, including the Soviet Union and China at the height of the Cold War, died on Jan. 26 in Manhattan. She was 102.

headline_main: Lucy Jarvis, Who Took TV Viewers Far and Wide, Dies at 102

abstract: At Simon & Schuster, best sellers were her stock in trade. She popularized the nonfiction political page turner, starting with “All the President’s Men.”
snippet: At Simon & Schuster, best sellers were her stock in trade. She popularized the nonfiction political page turner, starting with “All the President’s Men.”
lead_paragraph: Alice Mayhew, a widely admired editor who shepherded into print best sellers by a veritable who’s who of writers — along the way popularizing the Washington political narrative, beginning with “All the President’s Men” in 1974 — died on Tuesday at her home in Manhattan. She was 87.

headline_main: Alice Mayhew, Who Edited a Who’s Who of Writers, Dies at 87

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Tom Steyer on Monday said he expected to leave Iowa's first-in-the-nation caucuses "with momentum" that carries him later this month to Nevada and South Carolina, where he has shown more strength in opinion polls.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Tom Steyer on Monday said he expected to leave Iowa's first-in-the-nation caucuses "with momentum" that carries him later this month to Nevada and South Carolina, where he has shown more strength in opinion polls.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential contender Tom Steyer on Monday said he expected to leave Iowa's first-in-the-nation caucuses "with momentum" that carries him later this month to Nevada and South Carolina, where he has shown more strength in opinion polls.
headline_main: After Massive Spending Blitz, Democrat Steyer Looking for Iowa Boost
headline_print_headline: After Massive Spending Blitz, Democrat Steyer Looking for Iowa Boost

abstract: Scores of volunteers from across the United States descended on icy Iowa ahead of Monday's Democratic caucus with one goal: nominating a candidate who can defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.
snippet: Scores of volunteers from across the United States descended on icy Iowa ahead of Monday's Democratic caucus with one goal: nominating a candidate who can defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Scores of volunteers from across the United States descended on icy Iowa ahead of Monday's Democratic caucus with one goal: nominating a candidate who can defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.
headline_main: Volunteers Flock to Iowa for High-Stakes Democratic Nominating Contest
headline_print_headline: Volunteers Flock to Iowa for High-Stakes Democratic Nominating Contest

abstract: Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group Inc (MUFG), Japan's largest lender by assets, reported a net loss in the third quarter, for the first time in nearly a decade, as its banking unit booked a one-off charge on an Indonesian subsidiary.
snippet: Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group Inc (MUFG), Japan's largest lender by assets, reported a net loss in the third quarter, for the first time in nearly a decade, as its banking unit booked a one-off charge on an Indonesian subsidiary.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group Inc (MUFG), Japan's largest lender by assets, reported a net loss in the third quarter, for the first time in nearly a decade, as its banking unit booked a one-off charge on an Indonesian subsidiary.
headline_main: MUFG Reports First Quarterly Loss in Decade on Writedown at Indonesian Unit
headline_print_headline: MUFG Reports First Quarterly Loss in Decade on Writedown at Indonesian Unit

abstract: The inside story of the president and Deutsche Bank, his lender of last resort.
snippet: The inside story of the president and Deutsche Bank, his lender of last resort.
lead_paragraph: One Day in early 2017, Mike Offit went to the Yale Club in Manhattan for a lunch hosted by a group called Business Executives for National Security. Offit, who has a craggy face and shoulder-­length hair, had spent much of his career in banking, but that had ended nearly two decades earlier. Since then, he had puttered around the outskirts of finance, dabbled in journalism and even published a novel about a pair of murders at a fictional German-­owned Wall Street bank that bore a striking resemblance to the one that he worked for until 1998: ­Deutsche Bank.

abstract: A girl was killed and five other people were injured, three critically, when a motorist mourning the Sunday traffic death of his 29-year-old son slammed his vehicle into a high school cross-country team as they ran along a street outside their suburban Oklahoma City school Monday, officials said.
snippet: A girl was killed and five other people were injured, three critically, when a motorist mourning the Sunday traffic death of his 29-year-old son slammed his vehicle into a high school cross-country team as they ran along a street outside their sub...
lead_paragraph: MOORE, Okla. — A girl was killed and five other people were injured, three critically, when a motorist mourning the Sunday traffic death of his 29-year-old son slammed his vehicle into a high school cross-country team as they ran along a street outside their suburban Oklahoma City school Monday, officials said.
headline_main: 1 Killed, 5 Injured When a Vehicle Hits High School Students
